=== Demographics ===
===2020 census===
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], St. Joseph had a population of 51, with 16 households and 15 families residing in the community.<ref name="Census2020DP">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic Profile (DP1)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dp?get=NAME,DP1_0021P,DP1_0024P,DP1_0025C,DP1_0049C,DP1_0045C,DP1_0069C,DP1_0073C,DP1_0125P,DP1_0126P,DP1_0129P,DP1_0133P,DP1_0137P,DP1_0138P,DP1_0139P,DP1_0141P,DP1_0142P,DP1_0143P,DP1_0145P,DP1_0146P,DP1_0147C,DP1_0148C,DP1_0149C,DP1_0156C,DP1_0157C,DP1_0158C,DP1_0159P,DP1_0160P&for=place%3A70005&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref><ref name="Census2020PL">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Redistricting Data (Public Law 94-171)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/pl?get=NAME,P1_001N,P1_003N,P1_004N,P1_005N,P1_006N,P1_007N,P1_008N,P1_009N,P2_001N,P2_002N,H1_001N,H1_002N&for=place%3A70005&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref> The [[population density]] was 59.2 inhabitants per square mile (22.9/km<sup>2</sup>). There were 23 housing units at an average density of 26.7 per square mile (10.3/km<sup>2</sup>).<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

The median age was 61.2 years. 19.6% of residents were under the age of 18, and 27.5% were 65 years of age or older. 19.6% of residents were under the age of 20; 0.0% were between the ages of 20 and 24; 15.7% were from 25 to 44; 37.3% were from 45 to 64; and 27.5% were 65 years of age or older. For every 100 females, there were 54.5 males, and for every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 64.0 males age 18 and over. The gender makeup of the community was 35.3% male and 64.7% female.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

All residents lived in rural areas.<ref name="Census2020DHC">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics (DHC)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dhc?get=NAME,P2_002N,P2_003N&for=place%3A70005&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2023|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

Of the 16 households, 6.3% had children under the age of 18 living in them. 87.5% were [[Marriage|married-couple households]], 0.0% were cohabitating-couple households, 12.5% had a female householder with no spouse or partner present, and 0.0% had a male householder with no spouse or partner present. 6.3% of all households were non-families. About 6.3% of all households were made up of individuals, and 0.0% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

There were 23 housing units, of which 30.4% were vacant. The homeowner vacancy rate was 0.0% and the rental vacancy rate was 0.0%.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

